# Audio Files for Portfolio

## Setup Instructions

1. Add your background music file as `background.mp3` in this directory
2. Optionally, also add `background.ogg` for better browser compatibility

## Recommended Audio Settings

- **Format**: MP3 (primary) and OGG (fallback)
- **Bitrate**: 128kbps or lower for web optimization
- **Duration**: 2-5 minutes (will loop automatically)
- **Volume**: The player is set to 30% volume by default
- **Style**: Ambient, lo-fi, or instrumental music works best for portfolios

## File Structure
```
audio/
├── background.mp3  (required)
├── background.ogg  (optional, for better compatibility)
└── README.md
```

## Audio Sources
You can find royalty-free music at:
- Freesound.org
- Zapsplat.com
- YouTube Audio Library
- Pixabay Music

## Notes
- The audio player will appear in the bottom-right corner
- Audio auto-starts 1 second after entering the portfolio
- Users can toggle play/pause with the pink button
- The player is hidden during the loading screen